# Scanner-side ignore file for the validation corpus.
#
# 1. Its presence shadows the sibling .gitignore in the suppression loader
#    (.relixqignore wins), so the git-only `!vendor/` re-include there cannot
#    leak into scan behavior — the walker's default vendored-dir policy stays
#    authoritative (vendor/legacylib/sign.py is policy_excluded, not gated).
# 2. It excludes the harness metadata files below from the scan so the
#    ground-truth manifest (which is full of algorithm names) can never
#    produce findings about itself.
/expected-findings.yaml
/README.md
/.gitignore
